<br>
 I choose to make sure my posts are pretty well error-proofed and I try to stick to using good grammar and I try my best to avoid acronyms and abreviations (Like Seb, EQ, ROTWF etc) as I like to come across as a fairly well spoken person, which I can be, in real life.<br>
<br>
 I also have the advantage of having a decent grasp of the English language. I also check my messages to make sure there aren't any bad spelling mistakes or miss-types, and so on.<br>
<br>
 I truly dissagree that someone who decides against this is stupid, or lower than me, or not worthy of my attention. That's a pompous look on things and that is my firm opinion on that matter.<br>
<br>
 So long as the sentances aren't illegible and aren't so garbled that it hurts the eyes to read (and so long as there is some semblance of paragraphing, lack of this really makes the eyes sting) then it doesn't matter to me how bad the spelling or grammar is.<br>
<br>
 Not everyone is good at English. It's a skill like any other and it's not something you absolutely <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>have</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to be good at to get by in life, although it certainly helps.<br>
<br>
 I know someone who is very well spoken in real life but doesn't bother to post messages in the same way, simply because this media is the way it is. Talking is so much faster than typing, for most people, and we don't all have the time to spend on typing messages to make sure it's pristine and perfect for others to read.<br>
<br>
 So long as it gets the message accross, that's all that matters, I say.<br>
<br>
 Those who pick holes in other people's grammar in some attempt to put them down or make themselves look better than the target of their put-down really need to step back and look at the big picture.<br>
<br>
 If someone uses abusive language and comes accross as an immature person, even if it's only due to the way they type, then that is how they portray themselves and can be judged in that way.<br>
<br>
 But those who just aren't good, or refuse to spend the time to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>look</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> good don't always fall into this category.<br>
<br>
 So, I agree with the original poster, except that his grammar and spelling obviously isnt something he is bothered about, so the kind of remarks he is so angry about are exactly the ones that surely shouldn't bother him anyway? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 If you see what I mean <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
